caption: A really beautiful church, i mean all churches in Paris are beautiful, but this is special. In this church they have a couple of times a month certain events, musical events that your heart will enjoy.  It is beside the Oldest Tree in Paris, another must see place near the Notre Dame de Paris. Take your time to visit these places and if there is an event don't hesitate to check it out.

Some of the stones in its courtyard date back to the Romans. We recently attended a lovely concert here on a Saturday afternoon that I will never forget.
Wow , they have some concerts and it was so worth it ‚Ä¶ I enjoyed every minute
We saw a 5 piece orchestral set here, and it was one of the best experiences you can find in Paris. Would highly recommend.

Beautiful old church close to Notre Dame cathedral. The church is located among some pretty streets.
The icon of Mother Mary is said to have started weeping / tears forming on top of the icon months before the Notre Dame caught fire in 2019

√âglise Saint-Julien-le-Pauvre is a Melkite Greek Catholic parish church in Paris, and one of the city's oldest religious buildings. Built in Romanesque style during the 13th century, it is situated in the 5th arrondissement. Originally a Roman Catholic Church. Dedicated to two medieval French saints of the same name: Julien. "The poor" is said to originate from Julien of Le Mans, whose dedication to the cause of the poor was considered exemplary.
Attended a piano concert this evening. Perfect intimate seeing. Small and simple, yet beautiful historical church.

Within the Quartier latin, this church was built with the notre dame de Paris cathedral, it is one of the oldest religious building in Paris.  Amazing must see medieval church for melkite greek orthodox. It was dedicated to 2 french saints holding the name of julian.
Lovely Chopin concert by vituoso pianist  Junko Okozaki in this beautiful little Melkite church reputed to be the oldest in Paris

The church is small, interesting. They have wonderful concerts here, about $25 per ticket for adults, special price for students (maybe 12‚Ç¨). Although you can book tickets via an online ticket agency, I recommend booking through the church‚Äôs website. All I did was send an email regarding the concert I wanted and how many seats, and I received an email confirmation. When we arrived, we paid for the tickets at the door and had reserved seats in the front row! The concert was relatively short, no intermission. We had hot chocolate and a sandwich afterward at a caf√© on the √éle de la Cit√©.  LOVELY EVENING!
Over the years they‚Äôve had the most beautiful and valuable classical music concerts in Paris. Worth every penny!
So cute and small church where you can see the best views of Notre Dame
Magnificent church. It's a great acoustic to attend a concert.
Wonderful experience. Beautiful tenor. Excellent pianist.
was there for a concert.
Amazing old church of Melkite Greek Catholics in the neighborhood of Notre-Damme Cathedral.
Beautiful church hosting fantastic musical concerts in the evening. Extremely atmospheric. A must go.
Nice color grades, unique roof

I attended a wonderful piano concert of Chopin piano music. Flyers were posted all over St-Michel district and the 'box office' opened 1hr before the show. Great acoustics and lovely Eastern Catholic Rite feel to the church!  Beautifully adorned Eastern Style Church,  but despite the looks, it is technically is closer to Catholic Church than Orthodox. Was deeded to the Melkite Church in 1800's after being Roman Cathiolic for centuries.

Beautiful old church in Paris with the long and complicated history! Apparently one of the oldest in Paris, worth spending one or two hours studying the icons - especially during the concerts as many of the small classic life performance are organised here.

When walking on the Boulevard St Michel by the Blvd Saint Germain on a Sunday late afternoon, we saw a poster advertising a piano solo recital by Miho Nitta that same evening. We decided to buy tickets and were delighted that we did. The church provided an amazing  yet intimate space for the concert and, of course, is worth a visit whether there is a concert or not.

This was a wonderful treat. We heard the pianist Philippe Alegre play the piano for nearly one and a half hours. He had some real show stoppers in his performance. A great activity that I recommend people to engage.
Great concerts are held here. The poster was not very accurate, but you just imagine a virtuoso concert in a 12th-century church, one of the oldest in the country.
We attended a classical music performance which was superb. A beautiful venue.
Small church but interesting. The music adds to the atmosphere. If not for the concert it is not worth coming a long way to visit.

Not sure how often Miho performs at St. Julienne but follow the many advertisements posted all around the city. A unique experience we shall never forget. On a chilly night the church was heated and very comfortable. Miho was happy to sign autographs and pose for photos after the very moving performance. Rhapsody In Blue a real highlight.
Wonderful acoustics at this gorgeous small church. Solo pianist's concert was intimate and unforgettable in such a wonderful environment.
The outside of the church does not really reflect the outstanding greatness of the interior, especially the iconostasis.
I recommend to visit Saint-Julien-le-Pauvre is a Melkite Greek Catholic parish church in Paris, France, one of the city's oldest religious buildings. outstanding .
A very old church is a great place for the concerts they give(a lot of piano). Sound is fantastic and the ambiance intimate.
Very old catholic Greek church - older than its famous neighbor Notre Dame. The interior is very beautiful and interesting.
The best acoustics in Paris. Small and real in the center of a Paris surrounded by tourists. Go with time and with entrance to a concert. ...
A superb old church where one can hear outstanding music recitals.  Chopin is just beautiful!!
This church celebrates the mass in Lebanese Arabic and French. It is a Greek Catholic church.
